snippet.textDisplay:
The fist bump with his daughter brought me to tears. As a father to a beautiful 4 year old who does the same bump to me on a daily basis I cannot take this. My condolences to everyone who was affected by this horrible accident. I grew up watching Kobe and the lakers during the Phil Jackson era and I was never really into sports at all but when he was on the court it was just something special to watch and be a part of.

Take this as a reminder to not take life for granted and it’s many blessings no matter how little money you may have, how little hope, we must always be grateful for what and who we have because tomorrow is not promised. We love you Kobe,Gia and all who lost their lives and their families. This one is going to hurt for way too long. May you all Rest In Peace. Much Love.

snippet.textDisplay: I normally don't have a reaction to a celebrity death because I feel like I don't personally know them but Kobe death really hurt me, then finding out he died with his daughter, a mother and father died with their daughter, and a mother died with her daughter along with the pilot hit me hard. I'm a year younger then Kobe, I'm also a mother of 4, and I can just imagine the him and the other parents trying to protect their daughters, and each others daughters telling them everything will be ok, the pilot trying to encourage them saying that everything is going to be ok, all the while being scared themselves of what will happen if that helicopter crash. It's really hurtful and sad to think about.
